			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Taken from <a href="http://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/faq.vm#System%20Requirements" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sony's offical Game Requirements</a>
<br />

<br />
-Operating System: Windows 98/2000/ME/XP 
<br />
-Processor: 1GHz or greater 
<br />
-RAM: 512 MB 
<br />
-Video Card: DirectX 9 compatible. Pixel shader and vertex shader compatible hardware with 64 MB of texture memory 
<br />
-Sound Card: DirectSound compatible audio hardware 
<br />

<br />
Your screwed in the video card requirement.  You will be able to install and probably boot, but expect your animation to be in frames per Minute, not secs.
<br />

<br />
If you want to play, maybe look for a cheap ATI 9200... it'll play at the lowest levels and runs about $40-50.<br />_________________<br />Death chases you like Night chases Day</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
