			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've been playing in 12 hours sessions without a single reboot necessary.  They either fixed the memory leak since I started playing (about a week or so ago), or there wasn't one to begin with.  I heard there was a memory leak in Beta, but I definitely haven't experienced it.
<br />

<br />
Yep, you're hosed on the Vid Card requirement.  Gotta upgrade that.  Seriously, man, I wouldn't even *attempt* it on that vid card.  You're just gonna set yourself up for disappointment.
<br />

<br />
You can probably find a cheap upgrade, as was mentioned above.  Also, if at all possible (I know I'm probably preaching to the choir here), try to double your Ram.  I was zoning in 2-3 minutes with 512Mb of ram.  Enough to be frustrating.  I upgraded to a gig of ram, and now I zone in less than 10 seconds.  Something to think about, at least.
<br />

<br />
But the zoning speed isn't a showstopper.  You can probably live with that for the time being.  Your vid card, on the other hand....<br />_________________<br />EQ1:  Mujahid Mukhtaar - Arch Lich, Solusek Ro (Retired)
<br />
EQ2:  Mujahid Mukhtaar - Summoner, Mistmoore
<br />

<br />
