<br />

<br />
Also, how much free space do you have on your HD, and when was the last time you defragged?  Reason I ask is that most games can be pretty heavy in the file I/O department.  Each time a file is read and written, it tends to become more and more fragmented over time.  This is exacerbated if you have limited space to begin with, and is readily noticeable during zoning (since that is when most file I/O takes place).
<br />

<br />
Does the game begin to run slower and slower in general (slower and slower FPS, for example) or is it just your zoning times that get worse and worse?<br />_________________<br />EQ1:  Mujahid Mukhtaar - Arch Lich, Solusek Ro (Retired)
<br />
EQ2:  Mujahid Mukhtaar - Summoner, Mistmoore
<br />

<br />
